The National Executive Committee (NEC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), yesterday, pegged the nomination form for Kogi and Bayelsa State governorship elections at N20 million. The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) had fixed Nov. 16th for the elections. Briefing newsmen at the end of the 86th Emergency National Executive Council (NEC) meeting at the party’s headquarters in Abuja,  PDP National Publicity Secretary, Kola Ologbondiyan said the expression of interest form would be sold at N1 million. He added that women would get the nomination form free. When asked why the party decided to increase the price of the form, Ologbondiyan said the cost of conducting primary election was very high. He pledged that the party would conduct a free, fair and credible primary in Bayelsa and Kogi states to produce credible candidates. In a document signed by PDP National Organizing Secretary, Col. Austin Akobundu (rtd.), the party disclosed that sales and return of expression of interest/nomination forms would commence on Monday, June 24 and close on Wednesday, July 24 at the party’s national Secretariat in Abuja. PDP NEC pegs Kogi, Bayelsa guber nomination form at 20m No automatic ticket for Wada - PDP DPC fixes dates for Kogi, Bayelsa governorship primaries Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin